The Chief takes Pacassi out of the Bureau for a walk around Eastside. She is uncomfortable by the size and number of people in the enormous city, and reluctant to come along, but the Chief convinces her to go with them to a restaurant owned by one of the Mayekans who emigrated when Pacassi was young. They reveal that all those who came to DisCity have retained their culture and are still in touch with each other, but Pacassi is resistant to meeting them again. Finally, the Chief brings her to a building where they are beginning to construct a museum dedicated to Mayekâ€™s history, complete with parts salvaged from the original power plant. Pacassi finally becomes emotional and accepts the Chiefâ€™s support, glad that the city and its people will not be forgotten.

//You tour for a long time in Eastside and visit many places that Pacassi has never been to.
Mayek's memories don't belong to Pacassi alone anymore. They shall not be forgotten. Instead, more and more people will remember them.//
